  "texts": [
    "To prepare AAV libraries for sequencing, qPCR was performed on the extracted AAV genomes or cDNA to determine the cycle thresholds for each sample type to prevent overamplification.",
    "PCR amplification using equal primer pairs (1-8) (described in ref.",
    "22) was used to attach partial Illumina Read 1 and Read 2 sequences using Q5 Hot Start High-Fidelity 2× Master Mix with an annealing temperature of 65 °C for 20 s and an extension time of 60 s. Round one PCR products were purified using AMPure XP beads following the manufacturer's protocol and eluted in 25 μL UltraPure Water (Thermo Fisher Scientific).",
    "Then, 2 μL was used as input in a second round of PCR to attach on Illumina adapters and dual index primers (NEB, E7600S) for five PCR cycles using Q5 Hot Start-High-Fidelity 2× Master Mix with an annealing temperature of 65 °C for 20 s and an extension time of 60 s. The round two PCR products were purified using AMPure XP beads following the manufacturer's protocol and eluted in 25 μL UltraPure DNase/RNase-Free distilled water (Thermo Fisher Scientific).",
    "To quantify the amount of PCR products for NGS, an Agilent High Sensitivity DNA Kit (Agilent, 5067-4626) was used with an Agilent 2100 Bioanalyzer."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}